Q.6
Write a program in java to print the number-increasing reverse Pyramid Pattern.

Answer:
import java.util.*; 
  
public class GeeksForGeeks { 
  
    public static void printPattern(int n) 
    { 
        int i, j;       
        for (i = n; i >= 1; i--) {      
            for (j = 1; j <= i; j++) { 
                System.out.print(j + " "); 
            } 
            System.out.println(); 
        } 
    } 
    public static void main(String args[]) 
    { 
        int n = 6; 
        printPattern(n); 
    } 
}

O/P:
1 2 3 4 5 6 
1 2 3 4 5 
1 2 3 4 
1 2 3 
1 2 
1
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
Q.7
Write a program using break inside the innermost loop. But the loop breaks each time when j is equal to 2 and control goes to outer loop that starts from the next iteration.

Answer:

public class Demo{          
    public static void main(String[] args) {  
    	for(int i=1;i<=2;i++){  
            for (int j = 0; j <=3; j++) {
		if(j==2)
		 break;
		System.out.println(j);
		}          
        }  
    }  
}  

O/P:
0
1
0
1
-----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
Q.8
Compute the sum of 5 positive numbers.

Answer:

import java.util.Scanner;
public class Main {
  public static void main(String[] args) {
    Double number, sum = 0.0;
    Scanner input = new Scanner(System.in);
    for (int i = 1; i < 6; ++i) {
      System.out.print("Enter number " + i + " : ");
      number = input.nextDouble();
      if (number <= 0.0) {
        continue;
      }
      sum += number;
    }
    System.out.println("Sum = " + sum);
    input.close();
  }
}

O/P:
Enter number 1: 2.2
Enter number 2: 5.6
Enter number 3: 0
Enter number 4: -2.4
Enter number 5: -3
Sum = 7.8
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
Q.9
Program to find the sum of natural numbers from 1 to 1000.

Answer:

public class Main {
  public static void main(String[] args) {
      
    int sum = 0;
    int n = 1000;

    for (int i = 1; i <= n; ++i) {
      sum += i;    
    }
       
    System.out.println("Sum = " + sum);
  }
}

O/P: 
 Sum = 500500
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
Q.10
Given a list of integers, sort all the values present in it in descending order using Stream functions?
10,15,8,49,25,98,98,32,15.

Answer:
import java.util.*;
import java.util.stream.*;
import java.util.function.Function;

public class SortDescending{
  public static void main(String args[]) {
          List<Integer> myList = Arrays.asList(10,15,8,49,25,98,98,32,15);

           myList.stream()
           myList.sorted(Collections.reverseOrder())
           myList.forEach(System.out::println);
  }
}

O/P:
98
98
49
32
25
15
15
10
8
